10 SECTION 3. ACHIEVING CREDIT AND TRANSCRIPT MOBILITY. The Office of
11 the State Board of Education shall submit a report to the Joint Finance-Ap-
12 propriations Committee by December 31, 2025, detailing all appropriated
13 funds spent for the preceding five fiscal years, including federal and grant
14 funds, to achieve credit and/or transcript mobility for Idaho students.
15 This report shall identify outcomes and return on investment of appropriated
16 funds. The format and content of this report will be determined in con-
17 sultation with the Budget and Policy Analysis Division of the Legislative
18 Services Office.
19 SECTION 4. TRANSITIONING TO OUTCOMES-BASED FUNDING IN HIGHER EDU-
20 CATION. The Office of the State Board of Education shall develop an out-
21 comes-based funding model to replace the Enrollment Workload Adjustment
22 for Idaho's college and universities. The Office of the State Board of
23 Education shall deliver a written proposal to the Joint Finance-Appropria-
24 tions Committee by December 31, 2025, with a plan for implementation of the
25 new funding model in fiscal year 2028 or earlier. The Office of the State
26 Board of Education shall provide written reports to the Joint Finance-Ap-
27 propriations Committee on a quarterly basis detailing progress towards the
28 outcomes-based funding model. The format and content of this report will be
29 determined in consultation with the Budget and Policy Analysis Division of
30 the Legislative Services Office.
31 SECTION 5. TRANSITIONING TO OUTCOMES-BASED FUNDING IN HIGHER EDU-
32 CATION. The Office of the State Board of Education shall develop an out-
33 comes-based funding model to replace the Enrollment Workload Adjustment for
34 Idaho's community colleges. The Office of the State Board of Education shall
35 deliver a written proposal to the Joint Finance-Appropriations Committee by
36 December 31, 2025, with a plan for implementation of the new funding model
37 in fiscal year 2028 or earlier. The Office of the State Board of Education
38 shall provide written reports to the Joint Finance-Appropriations Committee
39 on a quarterly basis detailing progress towards the outcomes-based funding
40 model. The format and content of this report will be determined in con-
41 sultation with the Budget and Policy Analysis Division of the Legislative
42 Services Office.

